Introduction

Yoon Keeho is a South Korean-Canadian singer-songwriter, dancer, and composer under FNC Entertainment. He is best known as the leader and one of the visuals of the boy group P1Harmony,

Keeho is very popular on social networks thanks to his VLives in which he speaks a lot in English which makes it easier for international fans to understand. He is also popular for his cover of John Legend's "All of Me" on 10 January 2021 during the @P1uspace H: Get Together.

On September 16, Keeho was revealed as the fifth member of P1Harmony. The group officially debuted on October 28, 2020, with their first mini-album "Disharmony : Stand Out".
